cktop
=====

A Linux terminal system monitor. Reads directly from /proc.

Installation
------------

  go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/cktop@latest

Upgrade
-------

  GOPROXY=direct go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/cktop@latest


ckstat
======

A one-shot CLI tool that prints current memory usage.

Installation
------------

  go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/ckstat@latest

Usage
-----

  ckstat          # human-readable text
  ckstat -o json  # JSON output


ckagent
=======

A metrics agent that exposes system metrics in Prometheus exposition format.
Designed to be scraped by VictoriaMetrics (or Prometheus).

Installation
------------

  go install github.com/ckinan/cktop/cmd/ckagent@latest

Run
---

  ckagent -addr :9110

Metrics are available at http://localhost:9110/metrics.

VictoriaMetrics scrape config
-----------------------------

To scrape ckagent with VictoriaMetrics, create a scrape_config.yaml:

  scrape_configs:
    - job_name: ckagent
      static_configs:
        - targets: ['<host>:9110']
          labels:
            host: '<hostname>'

Pass it to VictoriaMetrics at startup:

  victoria-metrics-prod \
    -storageDataPath=<data_dir> \
    -promscrape.config=<path_to_scrape_config.yaml>

See https://docs.victoriametrics.com/victoriametrics/single-server-victoriametrics/ for full VictoriaMetrics configuration reference.

